==English==

===Etymology===
Attested as early as the early 18th century. The modern form of the expression first appeared in print as early as 1772. {{seeCites|en}}

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|en|it never rains but that it pours}}
* {{alter|en|when it rains, it pours}}

===Proverb===
{{en-proverb}}

# [[unfortunate|Unfortunate]] events occur in [[quantity]].
#: {{syn|en|misfortunes never come singly}}

====Coordinate terms====
* {{l|en|bad things come in threes}}

